Icterus gularis is a species of bird from the family Icteridae.
It is commonly known as the Altamira oriole. 
This bird has a distinctive bright orange-yellow plumage that covers its head, neck, breast, and belly.
Icterus gularis has a black back and wings with white patches on the wing feathers.
The beak of this bird is thick and slightly curved.
It has a pointed tail that is slightly longer than its body.
Icterus gularis can be found in the southern United States, Mexico, and Central America, typically inhabiting forests and woodlands.
